race.comment: TOO DARN STORMY (9) showed good promise in his 2YO season and looks to have returned in good order judging by his latest trials. Pike has been with him the whole way through and he draws beautifully. Looks to get every chance in the run and a positive return is on the cards. MARDUSA (8) comes here without a trial since his last start in the Sir Ernest Lee-Steere 63 days ago. CJP sticks with him though and he has shown some zip in the past. Watch for him flying late in the race. EARTH GOD (5) was strong from the front first-up at this track and it took a handy one to gun him down. This shapes similarly and he usually improves with the run under his belt. Can go on with the job now. LUCKY I AM (6) has enough early speed to roll across from out wide and the winkers replace the blinkers. Can turn in another forward showing. JUSTABITTAPRESS (7) is third-up not and can make his presence felt.
